    {
      "id": "2ab81d9dbac9ae3e4de3d14c4f11546f1a881130",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 441,
        "name": "Rahul Deshmukh",
        "email": "rahul.deshmukh@seagate.com",
        "username": "520557",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-06-25 10:53:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n> Is there any kind of file create benchmark (e.g. multi-client\n > mdtest or mdsrate) to see what the impact of this extra locking is?\n\nI think multi-client mdtest will be good test. But no such testing is done yet. I hope, I got the question, please help otherwise.\n\nOnly IOR + MPI test run where done to see if equal distribution is done or not. Sample out put of it like following (with fix in place):\n\n----------------------------------------------\nRun began: Mon Mar 23 02:28:56 2015\nCommand line used: /home/bloewe/benchmarks/IOR-2.10.3/src/C/IOR -a POSIX -B -C -E -F -e -g -k -b 200m -t 2m -o /mnt/lustre0/ceap-82/IOR_POSIX\nMachine: Linux sjsc-321\n\nSummary:\n\tapi                = POSIX\n\ttest filename      = /mnt/lustre0/ceap-82/IOR_POSIX\n\taccess             = file-per-process\n\tordering in a file = sequential offsets\n\tordering inter file=constant task offsets = 1\n\tclients            = 288 (24 per node)\n\trepetitions        = 1\n\txfersize           = 2 MiB\n\tblocksize          = 200 MiB\n\taggregate filesize = 56.25 GiB\n\nOperation  Max (MiB)  Min (MiB)  Mean (MiB)   Std Dev  Max (OPs)  Min (OPs)  Mean (OPs)   Std Dev  Mean (s)  \n---------  ---------  ---------  ----------   -------  ---------  ---------  ----------   -------  --------\nwrite        4427.20    4427.20     4427.20      0.00    2213.60    2213.60     2213.60      0.00  13.01049   EXCEL\nread        10026.62   10026.62    10026.62      0.00    5013.31    5013.31     5013.31      0.00   5.74471   EXCEL\n\nMax Write: 4427.20 MiB/sec (4642.25 MB/sec)\nMax Read:  10026.62 MiB/sec (10513.67 MB/sec)\n\nRun finished: Mon Mar 23 02:29:15 2015\n     24 0\n     24 1\n     24 2\n     24 3\n     24 4\n     24 5\n     24 6\n     24 7\n     24 8\n     24 9\n     24 10\n     24 11\n----------------------------------------------",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
